We have a win for Mother Earth. This year will be the first time fossil fuels make up less than half of the electricity generated in the UK. It's a "historic achievement", according to National Grid, and follows a dramatic decline in coal-fired power and rising renewable energy.

Instead, British homes and businesses will rely more on clean electricity generated by wind farms, solar panels, hydro power and nuclear power reactors.

